\section{Initial task}
\begin{frame}
  There's a game. It has a good physics engine at a specific domain.
  We need to reuse it for some other task. But the buit-in lua engine
  has limitations. It doesn't support extension with newly compiled modules.
  It doesn't have simple ways of building effective bindings for python.
  The most common language for machine learning.

  Let's reverse the game to get bindings for python.
\end{frame}

\section{What's been done}

\begin{frame}
  Results:
  \begin{enumerate}
    \item A way of communication with built-in lua for a C++ injected library;
    \item Python-bindings via message-queue between python and C++ module;
    \item Steam API has been stubbed, no need for an Steam account.
